   vulnerabilities:[], condImmunities:[],
   senses:"Darkvision 60 ft.; Passive Perception 10",
   languages:"Common, Elvish",
   desc:"Heralds of doom and plagues on the living, banshees are spirits obsessed by unresolved bitterness or sorrow. These phantoms slay any who glimpse them or hear their baleful wails. Elven communities particularly fear them.",
   traits:"Detect Life. The banshee magically senses the direction of creatures up to 1 mile away that aren't Constructs or Undead.\nIncorporeal Movement. The banshee can move through other creatures and objects as if they were Difficult Terrain. It takes 5 (1d10) Force damage if it ends its turn inside an object.",
   actions:"Multiattack. The banshee makes two Corrupting Touch attacks and uses Horrify.\nCorrupting Touch. Melee Attack Roll: +5, reach 5 ft. Hit: 7 (1d8+3) Necrotic damage.\nHorrify. Wisdom Saving Throw: DC 13, one creature within 60 feet that can see the banshee. Failure: The target has the Frightened condition until the start of the banshee's next turn.\nDeathly Wail (1/Day). The banshee releases a mournful wail if it isn't in sunlight. Constitution Saving Throw: DC 13, each creature within 30 feet that can hear the wail and isn't a Construct or Undead. Failure: If the target has 25 Hit Points or fewer, it drops to 0 HP. Otherwise it has the Frightened condition until the end of its next turn.",
